&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;strong&gt;memory leak&lt;/strong&gt; occurs when a program allocates memory dynamically (e.g., using &lt;code&gt;malloc&lt;/code&gt;) and fails to release it using &lt;code&gt;free&lt;/code&gt;. This leftover allocation can lead to wasted memory resources, eventually causing slowdowns or system crashes in long-running programs.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
